limitations: [
	{description: "Full bitemporal modeling (separate valid_time and transaction_time columns) adds significant schema and query complexity.", alternative: "MVP: event sourcing (transaction time built-in via event timestamps) + immutable records with corrections as new entries. Gives ~80% of bitemporal benefit. Full bitemporal with explicit valid_time: add when FIDC regulatory audit demands as-of queries that distinguish 'when it happened in reality' from 'when we learned about it.' Most queries: transaction time (event sourcing) is sufficient.", rationale: "Event sourcing gives transaction time for free. Valid time: add when regulatory demands. 80% of benefit, 20% of complexity."},
	{description: "Day count conventions vary by FIDC regulamento — one FIDC may require business/252, another actual/360.", alternative: "DayCountConvention as configuration per FIDC. Pricing function: accepts convention as parameter. Default: BUSINESS_252 (market standard). Override: per FIDC if regulamento specifies different. Pricing: deterministic given (rate, dates, convention). Convention: stored per operation for audit trail.", rationale: "Configuration, not hardcode. Most FIDCs: business/252. Allow override when contractually required."},
	{description: "Cutoff time alignment with banking partner may change (bank changes batch schedule) requiring coordination.", alternative: "Cutoff as configuration per banking partner. When partner changes batch time: update config (no code deploy). Buffer: 30+ minutes between Mesh cutoff and bank batch time. Monitor: if any operation misses bank batch despite being before Mesh cutoff → cutoff-bank alignment may be off → investigate with partner.", rationale: "Cutoff is partnership-dependent. Config + buffer + monitoring: handles changes."},
	{description: "Timezone handling adds conceptual complexity to every temporal operation — developers must always think about 'which timezone?'", alternative: "Strict discipline reduces complexity to 3 points: UTC everywhere except cutoff check, vintage assignment, and display. After initial setup and CLAUDE.md instruction: timezone is mechanical. Developer: 'am I at one of the 3 conversion points? If yes: use BRT. If no: UTC.' Library handles all complexity (DST, transitions). Manual thinking: minimal after setup.", rationale: "Upfront discipline eliminates ongoing complexity. 3 conversion points: memorizable. Rest: UTC by default."},
	{description: "Property-based testing with 10,000 temporal inputs requires comprehensive holiday data for test years — if holiday data is wrong, tests validate against wrong calendar.", alternative: "Use same holiday data source for test and production: Banco Central published calendar. Holiday data IS test data. Update both: annually, from same source. If data is wrong in test: it's also wrong in production → bug is real, not test artifact. Additional: cross-reference with 2 sources for validation.", rationale: "Same data source for test and production. PBT quality = calendar data quality. Both must be correct."},
]

rationale: "Sistemas financeiros são profundamente temporais — datas de vencimento, janelas de liquidação, períodos de carência, contagem de dias, fusos horários, safras. Erros temporais acumulam: settlement errado × volume = dinheiro no lugar errado; day count errado × volume = overcharging milhares de reais/mês; timezone errado × vintage = analytics distorcida para decisão de FIDC. Na Mesh, esta lens operacionaliza: primitivas temporais com type discipline rigorosa — Instant para eventos, LocalDate para business dates, NEVER VARCHAR (temporal type discipline 2024+, vencimento ≠ timestamp 2024+), janelas de liquidação com chain completa de timezone→cutoff→business day (settlement calculation chain 2024+, cutoff time 2024+), modelagem bitemporal para audit e compliance regulatória (Snodgrass 2000, as-of query), contagem de dias com convention explícita alinhada ao contrato (ISDA standards, business/252 padrão brasileiro, day count matters 2024+), cutoffs e ciclos de batch com boundaries temporais claros e período immutable (operational time boundaries 2024+, period immutability 2024+), disciplina de timezone com UTC everywhere e 3 pontos de conversão explícitos (UTC single source 2024+, conversion points 2024+), testes de integridade temporal com 6 property-based tests (temporal PBT 2024+), e análise de safra/cohort com timezone-aware vintage assignment (vintage analysis, maturation curve 2024+, temporal grain 2024+). Tempo é primitiva de primeira classe em sistema financeiro: erros temporais são erros financeiros — não bugs de UX, mas dinheiro no lugar errado."

}
